## Running on BrowserStack

This project ships with the BrowserStack SDK pre-wired. To run your tests on
BrowserStack's cloud instead of locally:

1. Sign up at https://www.browserstack.com/ (free trial available).
2. Grab your username + access key from https://www.browserstack.com/accounts/settings
3. Export them as env vars before running:

   ```bash
   export BROWSERSTACK_USERNAME=your_username
   export BROWSERSTACK_ACCESS_KEY=your_access_key
   ```

4. (Optional) Edit `browserstack.yml` (at the project root — the SDK hard-codes
   this path) to customise the platform matrix,
   build name, or enable BrowserStack Local for staging URLs behind a firewall.
5. Run tests the same way — the SDK intercepts the Selenium driver automatically:

   ```bash
   mvn test
   ```

6. Watch the session live at https://automate.browserstack.com/

**Local fallback:** when `BROWSERSTACK_USERNAME` isn't set, the SDK passes
through to the standard local driver so the same codebase works both ways.

{{/if}}
